 <text>
  <front>
   <head>SONG to CLOE, playing on her Spinet.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="tetrameter">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">WHEN  strikes the trembling Strings,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Applauding  round her fly;</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Exulting clap their little Wings</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Bask'd in the Sun-shine of her Eye.</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+" line_length="4">The Graces too,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+" line_length="4">As others do,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">In Raptures stand to hear,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Time stays his flagging Wings, and adds,</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">One Hour to the rolling Year:</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+" line_length="4">Keep off, ye Beaus,</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+" line_length="4">For who but knows</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">That  Eyes can wound?</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">If those you miss — yet pray avoid</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The Danger of enchanting Sound.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="tetrameter">
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">led the ravish'd Stones</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">(They say) — and as he'd rise or fall,</l>
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Bricks, Pebbles, Slats, and Marrow-Bones</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Wou'd form a Steeple or a Wall:</l>
     <l n="19" met="-+|-+" line_length="4">But this, you know,</l>
     <l n="20" met="-+|-+" line_length="4">Is long ago:</l>
     <l n="21" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">We fancy 'tis a Whim:</l>
     <l n="22" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">O had they charming  heard,</l>
     <l n="23" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">They'd surely not have stir'd for him.</l>
     <l n="24" met="-+|-+" line_length="4">The  Bard,</l>
     <l n="25" met="-+|-+" line_length="4">Whose Fate was hard,</l>
     <l n="26" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">(And  severe)</l>
     <l n="27" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Had brought  back — alas!</l>
     <l n="28" met="-+-+|-+" line_length="6">But  was not there.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
